==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: plains wanderer
<hw>plains wanderer</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A bird of the genus
<gen>Pedionomus</gen> (<spn>Pedionomus torquatus</spn>) of New South
Wales, the only species in the genus. <gen>Pedionomus</gen> is the only
genus of the family <fam>Pedionomidae</fam> of the order
<ord>Passeriformes</ord> and the plains wanderer is thus the only
species in the family. The total world population (ca. 2000) is
estimated to be 5 to 10 thousand.</def> <note>See also
http://www.philipmaher.com/plains.htm.</note>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> plain wanderer.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plaint</ent>⟦br⟧
